        <div class="row"><div class="column text"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Mon, 29 Jun 2026 14:24:26 GMT">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Mon, 29 Jun 2026 14:24:26 GMT">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Mark Sherman, Associated Press, Local 4">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static14/politics/2026/06/29/supreme-court-says-feds-cook-can-keep-her-job-for-now-but-it-upholds-other-trump-firings.webp" alt="Supreme Court says Fed&#8217;s Cook can keep her job for now, but it upholds other Trump firings" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Supreme Court says Fed&#8217;s Cook can keep her job for now, but it upholds other Trump firings</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      The Supreme Court says Federal Reserve governor Lisa Cook can remain in her job for now, a rebuke to President Donald Trump’s bid to wrest control of the nation’s central bank.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/politics/2026/06/29/supreme-court-says-feds-cook-can-keep-her-job-for-now-but-it-upholds-other-trump-firings/"  >(Mark Sherman, Associated Press, Local 4)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Mon, 29 Jun 2026 18:17:23 GMT">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Mon, 29 Jun 2026 18:17:23 GMT">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Michael Kunzelman, Associated Press, KPRC 2">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static14/politics/2026/06/29/dc-will-pay-50000-to-man-detained-while-protesting-guard-patrol-with-star-wars-song-record-says.webp" alt="DC will pay $50,000 to man detained while protesting guard patrol with 'Star Wars' song, record says" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">DC will pay $50,000 to man detained while protesting guard patrol with 'Star Wars' song, record says</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      A settlement document reveals the District of Columbia has agreed to pay $50,000 to resolve a lawsuit filed by a resident who accused police officers of illegally detaining him for following an Ohio National Guard patrol while playing Darth Vader’s theme song from “Star Wars” on his phone.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/politics/2026/06/29/dc-will-pay-50000-to-man-detained-while-protesting-guard-patrol-with-star-wars-song-record-says/"  >(Michael Kunzelman, Associated Press, KPRC 2)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Mon, 29 Jun 2026 12:33:46 GMT">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Mon, 29 Jun 2026 12:33:46 GMT">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Associated Press, KPRC 2">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static14/politics/2026/06/29/the-latest-trump-says-iran-wants-a-meeting-tehran-says-nothings-scheduled.webp" alt="Live updates: Supreme Court lets Trump fire agency heads, a dramatic expansion of presidential power" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Live updates: Supreme Court lets Trump fire agency heads, a dramatic expansion of presidential power</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      President Donald Trump has won and lost some as the Supreme Court wraps its final week of a term focused on executive power.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/politics/2026/06/29/the-latest-trump-says-iran-wants-a-meeting-tehran-says-nothings-scheduled/"  >(Associated Press, KPRC 2)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
</div><div class="column hcwi"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Tue, 23 Jun 2026 20:22:17 GMT">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Tue, 23 Jun 2026 20:22:17 GMT">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="The Associated Press, MPR News">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static14/politics/2026/06/23/senate-approves-war-powers-resolution-rebuking-trump-over-iran-conflict.webp" alt="Senate approves war powers resolution rebuking Trump over Iran conflict" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Senate approves war powers resolution rebuking Trump over Iran conflict</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      The Senate for the first time has approved a war powers resolution to block U.S. military action against Iran. Tuesday's vote comes as lawmakers warily watch President Donald Trump’s efforts to resolve the conflict.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/politics/2026/06/23/senate-approves-war-powers-resolution-rebuking-trump-over-iran-conflict/"  >(The Associated Press, MPR News)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Mon, 29 Jun 2026 10:33:05 GMT">
